   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Observability — Monitoring Cache Performance\n",
    "\n",
    "Understanding how well your cache is performing is essential for:\n",
    "- **Justifying the cache** — is the hit rate high enough?\n",
    "- **Tuning thresholds** — should `score_threshold_semantic` be raised or lowered?\n",
    "- **Diagnosing latency** — which tier is slow?\n",
    "- **Capacity planning** — how fast is the collection growing?\n",
    "\n",
    "Medha 0.3.0 collects per-request statistics when `collect_stats=True` (default).\n",
    "Call `await medha.stats()` at any time to get a `CacheStats` snapshot.\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook covers:\n",
    "1. **Enabling stats** — `collect_stats=True`\n",
    "2. **Generating traffic** — store + search mix\n",
    "3. **Interpreting `CacheStats`** — hit rate, latency percentiles, by-strategy\n",
    "4. **`reset_stats()`** — rolling windows\n",
    "5. **Disabling stats** — `collect_stats=False`\n",
    "6. **`stats_max_latency_samples`** — buffer size and memory impact\n",
    "7. **Mini dashboard** — print stats every N searches\n",
    "8. **Prometheus hint** — mapping stats to metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "**Requirements:** `pip install \"medha-archai[fastembed]\"`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import asyncio\n",
    "\n",
    "from medha import Medha, Settings\n",
    "from medha.embeddings.fastembed_adapter import FastEmbedAdapter\n",
    "\n",
    "embedder = FastEmbedAdapter(model_name=\"BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5\", cache_dir=\"./.fastembed_cache\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 1: Enable Stats + Store 5 Entries + 10 Searches → `stats()`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "settings = Settings(\n",
    "    backend_type=\"memory\",\n",
    "    collect_stats=True,  # enabled by default\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "pairs = [\n",
    "    (\"How many users are there?\",      \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users\"),\n",
    "    (\"List all active users\",          \"SELECT * FROM users WHERE status = 'active'\"),\n",
    "    (\"Average salary by department\",   \"SELECT dept, AVG(salary) FROM employees GROUP BY dept\"),\n",
    "    (\"Top 10 products by revenue\",     \"SELECT product_id, SUM(amount) FROM orders GROUP BY product_id ORDER BY 2 DESC LIMIT 10\"),\n",
    "    (\"Orders placed today\",            \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM orders WHERE DATE(created_at) = CURDATE()\"),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "search_mix = [\n",
    "    \"How many users are there?\",           # L1 hit (exact repeat)\n",
    "    \"How many users are there?\",           # L1 hit again\n",
    "    \"Total number of registered users\",    # semantic hit\n",
    "    \"Show all active members\",             # semantic hit\n",
    "    \"Average pay per team\",                # semantic hit\n",
    "    \"Best selling products\",               # semantic hit\n",
    "    \"Recent order volume\",                 # semantic hit\n",
    "    \"Something completely unrelated A\",    # miss\n",
    "    \"Something completely unrelated B\",    # miss\n",
    "    \"Something completely unrelated C\",    # miss\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "async with Medha(\"obs_demo\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as medha:\n",
    "    for q, sql in pairs:\n",
    "        await medha.store(q, sql)\n",
    "\n",
    "    for q in search_mix:\n",
    "        await medha.search(q)\n",
    "\n",
    "    stats = await medha.stats()\n",
    "    print(stats)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 2: Interpreting `CacheStats`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "settings = Settings(backend_type=\"memory\", collect_stats=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "async with Medha(\"obs_interp\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as medha:\n",
    "    for q, sql in pairs:\n",
    "        await medha.store(q, sql)\n",
    "    for q in search_mix:\n",
    "        await medha.search(q)\n",
    "\n",
    "    s = await medha.stats()\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(\"=== CacheStats breakdown ===\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  total_requests : {s.total_requests}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  total_hits     : {s.total_hits}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  total_misses   : {s.total_misses}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  hit_rate       : {s.hit_rate:.2%}  ← target > 70%\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  miss_rate      : {s.miss_rate:.2%}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  backend_count  : {s.backend_count}  entries in vector store\")\n",
    "    print()\n",
    "    print(\"  Latency percentiles (ms):\")\n",
    "    print(f\"    p50  : {s.latency_p50_ms:.2f}ms\")\n",
    "    print(f\"    p95  : {s.latency_p95_ms:.2f}ms\")\n",
    "    print(f\"    p99  : {s.latency_p99_ms:.2f}ms\")\n",
    "    print()\n",
    "    print(\"  By strategy:\")\n",
    "    for strategy, st in s.by_strategy.items():\n",
    "        print(f\"    {strategy:<20s} count={st.count:>3d}  avg={st.avg_latency_ms:.2f}ms\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 3: `reset_stats()` — Rolling Windows"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "settings = Settings(backend_type=\"memory\", collect_stats=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "async with Medha(\"obs_reset\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as medha:\n",
    "    for q, sql in pairs:\n",
    "        await medha.store(q, sql)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Window 1\n",
    "    for q in search_mix[:5]:\n",
    "        await medha.search(q)\n",
    "    s1 = await medha.stats()\n",
    "    print(f\"Window 1: requests={s1.total_requests}  hit_rate={s1.hit_rate:.2%}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Reset — start a new measurement window\n",
    "    await medha.reset_stats()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Window 2\n",
    "    for q in search_mix[5:]:\n",
    "        await medha.search(q)\n",
    "    s2 = await medha.stats()\n",
    "    print(f\"Window 2: requests={s2.total_requests}  hit_rate={s2.hit_rate:.2%}\")\n",
    "    print(\"(reset_stats() zeroes counters and latency buffer)")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 4: `collect_stats=False` — Zero Overhead Mode"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "settings = Settings(backend_type=\"memory\", collect_stats=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "async with Medha(\"obs_off\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as medha:\n",
    "    await medha.store(\"User count\", \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users\")\n",
    "    await medha.search(\"How many users?\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    s = await medha.stats()\n",
    "    print(f\"collect_stats=False → total_requests={s.total_requests}  (all zeros)\")\n",
    "    print(f\"hit_rate={s.hit_rate:.2%}  by_strategy={s.by_strategy}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `stats_max_latency_samples` — Buffer Size and Memory Impact\n",
    "\n",
    "`stats_max_latency_samples` controls the size of the FIFO latency buffer used\n",
    "to compute P50/P95/P99 percentiles.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Setting | Memory (float64) | Behavior |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| 1 000 (min) | ~8 KB | Percentiles computed over last 1k requests |\n",
    "| 10 000 (default) | ~80 KB | Good balance for most workloads |\n",
    "| 100 000 | ~800 KB | Smooth percentiles for high-QPS systems |\n",
    "| 1 000 000 (max) | ~8 MB | High precision, high memory cost |\n",
    "\n",
    "When the buffer is full, the oldest sample is evicted (FIFO) — percentiles\n",
    "always reflect the most recent `stats_max_latency_samples` requests."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 5: Mini Dashboard — Print Stats Every 5 Searches"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "settings = Settings(\n",
    "    backend_type=\"memory\",\n",
    "    collect_stats=True,\n",
    "    stats_max_latency_samples=10_000,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "dashboard_questions = [\n",
    "    \"How many users are there?\",\n",
    "    \"Total user count\",\n",
    "    \"List active users\",\n",
    "    \"Show active members\",\n",
    "    \"Top revenue products\",\n",
    "    \"Best selling items\",\n",
    "    \"Orders today\",\n",
    "    \"Daily order count\",\n",
    "    \"Something random 1\",\n",
    "    \"Something random 2\",\n",
    "    \"Something random 3\",\n",
    "    \"Something random 4\",\n",
    "    \"Average pay\",\n",
    "    \"Mean salary\",\n",
    "    \"Highest priced product\",\n",
    "    \"Most expensive item\",\n",
    "    \"Unknown query A\",\n",
    "    \"Unknown query B\",\n",
    "    \"Unknown query C\",\n",
    "    \"Unknown query D\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "async with Medha(\"dashboard\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as medha:\n",
    "    for q, sql in pairs:\n",
    "        await medha.store(q, sql)\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"  {'#':>3s}  {'hit_rate':>9s}  {'p50':>7s}  {'p95':>7s}  {'backend':>7s}\")\n",
    "    print(\"  \" + \"-\" * 44)\n",
    "\n",
    "    for i, q in enumerate(dashboard_questions, start=1):\n",
    "        await medha.search(q)\n",
    "        if i % 5 == 0:\n",
    "            s = await medha.stats()\n",
    "            print(\n",
    "                f\"  {i:>3d}  {s.hit_rate:>8.1%}  \"\n",
    "                f\"{s.latency_p50_ms:>5.1f}ms  \"\n",
    "                f\"{s.latency_p95_ms:>5.1f}ms  \"\n",
    "                f\"{s.backend_count:>7d}\"\n",
    "            )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Prometheus Integration — Future Roadmap\n",
    "\n",
    "Medha 0.3.0 does not ship a Prometheus exporter, but `CacheStats` maps cleanly\n",
    "to standard Prometheus metric types:\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "from prometheus_client import Counter, Histogram\n",
    "\n",
    "# Counter — total requests per strategy\n",
    "cache_requests = Counter(\n",
    "    \"medha_cache_requests_total\",\n",
    "    \"Total cache requests\",\n",
    "    [\"strategy\"],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Histogram — search latency\n",
    "search_latency = Histogram(\n",
    "    \"medha_search_latency_seconds\",\n",
    "    \"Search latency\",\n",
    "    buckets=[0.001, 0.005, 0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.5, 1.0],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# After each search:\n",
    "cache_requests.labels(strategy=hit.strategy.value).inc()\n",
    "search_latency.observe(elapsed_seconds)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "The `by_strategy` breakdown in `CacheStats` maps directly to the `strategy` label."
   ]
  }
